1. you have deployed the EC2 instance via the auto scaling group. so it is having the application traffic for your production workload. So suddenly, the EC2, whichever launched from auto-scaling, launched and terminated within five minutes. The cycle is repeating frequently due to the health check issue. you need to review the instance, why it is failing the health checks, and wanted to retain the log from the failed instance to know for the investigation. So how do you achieve this?

Step 1 — Put instance in Standby mode immediately:

# Stop Auto Scaling from terminating the instance
aws autoscaling enter-standby \
  --instance-ids i-1234567890 \
  --auto-scaling-group-name my-asg \
  --should-decrement-desired-capacity

# Now instance stays alive
# Auto Scaling won't touch it
# You can investigate freely

In UI

Go to AWS Console
Search → EC2
Left side → Auto Scaling Groups
Click → your ASG name

Click → Instance management tab
        (bottom section)
        │
        ▼
You see list of all instances
Select → the problematic instance
        (checkbox on left)
        │
        ▼
Click → Actions button (top)
Click → Set to Standby
        │
        ▼
Popup appears:
"Decrement desired capacity?" 
Select → Yes
Click → Set to Standby

