how would you restrict S3 access to only VPC traffic?

Concept:

Without restriction:
Anyone on internet → can access S3 ❌

With VPC restriction:
Only traffic from your VPC → can access S3 ✅
Internet traffic → denied ❌

You need S3 Bucket Policy with VPC condition.

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:*",
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket/*"
      ],
      "Condition": {
        "StringNotEquals": {
          "aws:SourceVpc": "vpc-12345678"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
-----------
What this does:

Anyone NOT coming from vpc-12345678
        │
        ▼
DENY all S3 actions
        │
        ▼
Internet traffic → blocked ✅
VPC traffic      → allowed ✅
